le it’s called American lobster, this species is found as far south as North Carolina in the US all the way to Labrador in northern Canada. In fact, in Canada, 97% of lobster fisheries are MSC certified. Known for its firm, sweet meat, American lobster holds up well to a variety of cooking styles, and no one can agree on whether the claw or tail meat is better!", "image": "records/th.jpeg", "date_of_creation": "2023-01-27T14:14:17.976Z", "id_public": true, "views_controller": 0}}]